{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e55f188a-e2f9-459b-85f6-cb61698d8781","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading files via property functions executes during **every evaluation** (design-time, restore, build). This blocks the evaluation thread with disk I/O. **Fix:** Move file reading to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs at build time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Expensive Glob Pattern (Medium Impact)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nA recursive `**\\*.*` glob walks the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. If this directory grows (e.g., `node_modules`, large asset folders), evaluation time balloons. **Fix:** Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to exclude known large directories, or narrow the glob to specific extensions/subdirectories.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels of chained imports (on top of SDK imports). Each import adds evaluation overhead. While 3 levels is modest, this pattern can grow. **Fix:** Flatten where possible or consolidate into a single shared `.props` file.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Remedy |\n|-------|----------|--------|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | 🔴 High | Move to a build-time target |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | 🟡 Medium | Narrow scope or add exclusions |\n| Nested import chain | 🟢 Low | Flatten imports |\n\nThe file I/O property function is the most impactful — it forces synchronous disk reads on every IDE evaluation pass.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1342ea5b-dcac-491b-a193-518cc4911c41","outputTokens":461,"requestId":"0413:5DFE:B1F24A:CF59CA:69F2AEFA"},"id":"477d33a1-49be-45bd-abf1-6af5474d0743","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:23:18.267Z","parentId":"395a347e-a2e9-4a09-b918-5dd4a181d78e"}
